import pandas as pd
df = pd.read_csv('/content/drive/My Drive/covid_19_data.csv',parse_dates=['Last Update'],index_col=0) 
#parsing according to the last update datetime column
#serial number as index
df.rename(columns={'ObservationDate':'Date', 'Country/Region':'Country'}, inplace=True)
#renaming certain columns
In [0]:
#used for Map later
df_confirmed = pd.read_csv("/content/drive/My Drive/time_series_covid_19_confirmed.csv")
df_confirmed.rename(columns={'Country/Region':'Country'}, inplace=True)
df_confirmed = df_confirmed[["Province/State","Lat","Long","Country"]]
df_temp = df.copy()
df_temp['Country'].replace({'Mainland China': 'China'}, inplace=True)
df_latlong = pd.merge(df_temp, df_confirmed, on=["Country", "Province/State"])

import plotly.graph_objects as go
fig = go.Figure()
fig.add_trace(go.Bar(x=confirmed['Date'],
                y=confirmed['Confirmed'],
                name='Confirmed',
                marker_color='blue'
                ))
fig.add_trace(go.Bar(x=deaths['Date'],
                y=deaths['Deaths'],
                name='Deaths',
                marker_color='Red'
                ))
fig.add_trace(go.Bar(x=recovered['Date'],
                y=recovered['Recovered'],
                name='Recovered',
                marker_color='Green'
                ))

fig.update_layout(title='Worldwide Corona Virus Cases - Confirmed, Deaths, Recovered (Bar Chart)',
    xaxis_tickfont_size=14,
    yaxis=dict(
        title='Number of Cases',
        titlefont_size=16,
        tickfont_size=14,
    ),
    legend=dict(
        x=0,
        y=1.0,
        bgcolor='rgba(255, 255, 255, 0)',
        bordercolor='rgba(255, 255, 255, 0)'
    ),
    barmode='group',
    bargap=0.15, # gap between bars of adjacent location coordinates.
    bargroupgap=0.1 # gap between bars of the same location coordinate.
)
fig.show()
#steep rise in confirmed cases around 12th March 2020. Reason could be more tests and results

Prophet Algorithm¶

Worldwide - Confirmed Cases¶

from fbprophet import Prophet
In [0]:
#Fixing data for forecasting
confirmed = df.groupby('Date').sum()['Confirmed'].reset_index()
confirmed.columns = ['ds','y']
confirmed['ds'] = pd.to_datetime(confirmed['ds'])
confirmed['cap']= 10000000
confirmed.head()

m = Prophet(interval_width=0.95,growth = 'logistic',n_changepoints=5)
m.fit(confirmed)
future = m.make_future_dataframe(periods=200)
future.tail()

import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import datetime as dt
from datetime import timedelta
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV

In [0]:
covid = pd.read_csv('/content/drive/My Drive/covid_19_data.csv')
In [0]:
#Dropping column as SNo is of no use, and "Province/State" contains too many missing values
covid.drop(["SNo"],1,inplace=True)
In [0]:
#Converting "Observation Date" into Datetime format
covid["ObservationDate"]=pd.to_datetime(covid["ObservationDate"])
In [0]:
#Grouping different types of cases as per the date
datewise=covid.groupby(["ObservationDate"]).agg({"Confirmed":'sum',"Recovered":'sum',"Deaths":'sum'})
In [0]:
datewise["Days Since"]=datewise.index-datewise.index[0]
datewise["Days Since"]=datewise["Days Since"].dt.days
In [0]:
train_ml=datewise.iloc[:int(datewise.shape[0]*0.90)]
valid_ml=datewise.iloc[int(datewise.shape[0]*0.90):]
model_scores=[]
